My name is Father Azerun.  I must apologize for my tardiness in coming to this most hospitible tavern, but duties in the world of Norrath have not allowed me the time or ability to venture into this timeless space and visit with each of you as perhaps I should have.<br>
<br>
   Many of you may know me from your encounters with me (Azerun Oldfather) in Norrath; I am fortunate enough to have been asked to be the leader of one of the older guilds in Norrath, The Hand of Mana, after our founder, Desferous, retired to places elsewhere. (We began in November of the Earth year 1999)<br>
<br>
   Since I am just arrived, I do not wish to be tedious (or heopfully, no more so than normal!) by discussing my personal history, although my history and the history of many of my colleagues may be found on our old website, <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://handofmana.home.mindspring.com.">handofmana.home.mindspring.com.</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END-->  We are slowly moving our information over to our named website, <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.handofmana.com,">www.handofmana.com,</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> along with our skill guides and other materials; but as we often are quite busy in Norrath, sometimes our representation through the outer world suffers as a result.  Since we often work much on learning the lore of Norrath and have a large percentage of masters and grandmasters of most trade skills (Indeed, if one could overcome a dragon by telling it bad puns in all the different languages of Norrath or by making its stomach explode by feeding it too many barbarian cookies, the Hand would be seen on planar raids today.)<br>
<br>
   I have looked through the names on these boards and seen many colleeagues, and many, I hope, new friends to be found.  My thanks for letting me curl up next to the fire. . . as a Gatecaller, and one without yet having the blessings of a Journeyman, my poor old feet remain tired after this long journey.  May the spirit of Saint Vanear remain within all of us, so that we may find our centers.<br>
<br>
<br>
Father Azerun<br>
Guild Leader, The Hand of Mana<br>
Lay minister of the Tranquil<br>
